Extract and Analyze Breach Data Using Dehashed
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Query breach databases using API tools and Python scripts
Analyze extracted breach data to identify security vulnerabilities
Detect sensitive information patterns in compromised data
Generate risk assessments and security recommendations
Create automated scripts for breach data analysis
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line operations
Fundamental Python programming skills
Understanding of JSON data structures
Knowledge of cybersecurity and data breach concepts
Familiarity with ethical hacking principles
Note: This lab uses mock data for educational purposes. All breach data is fictional and created for training only.

Lab Environment
This lab runs on a single Linux machine provided by Al Nafi. Click Start Lab to access your pre-configured environment. All tools and scripts will be created and executed on this machine.

